<!--
  RopQA Demo Release — ERN 4.3 with Intentional Errors
  =====================================================
  This file is used in the RopQA onboarding demo to showcase what
  the scanner catches. It contains 4 intentional errors:

  ERROR 1 (metadata layer): Track 2 is missing the MusicPublisher contributor.
           Rule: DDEX_PUBLISHER_REQUIRED — Every SoundRecording must have at
           least one Contributor with Role=MusicPublisher.
           Fix: Add a Contributor/MusicPublisher to Track 2.

  ERROR 2 (artwork layer): Cover art is 2000×2000 px.
           Rule: ART_MIN_RESOLUTION — Artwork must be at least 3000×3000 px
           for Spotify, Apple Music, and Amazon.
           Fix: Resize artwork to 3000×3000 or larger.

  ERROR 3 (ddex layer): Track 3 has a malformed ISRC (missing hyphens).
           Rule: DDEX_ISRC_FORMAT — ISRC must match CC-XXX-YY-NNNNN.
           Fix: Change USRC11607841X to US-RC1-16-07841.

  ERROR 4 (fraud layer): Track 3 has suspiciously generic lyrics keywords
           in the title and very short duration (under 60 seconds).
           Rule: FRAUD_MUSIC_SPAM — Short tracks with generic titles are a
           known signal for streaming fraud / artificial inflation.
           Fix: Review track; flag if content is not legitimate.
-->
